claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: A table displaying percentages of solicited adverse events (local and systemic) by severity (any, moderate, severe) across multiple study groups, with footnotes referencing Studies 2 and 4 and U.S.-licensed IIV3 vaccines. The table does not mention Flublok quadrivalent or Fluarix quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine and instead shows reactogenicity data without specifying those vaccines, so it does not support the claim.
